---
// src/pages/terms.astro
// DRAFT — plain-English beta Terms of Service. This is a reasonable
// starting point that reflects the current product reality. Before any
// serious launch you should replace this with output from a legal
// generator like Termly or iubenda (see https://termly.io).
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 12, 2026';
---
<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Skilly"
  description="Terms of service for the Skilly Beta."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-28 lg:pt-36 pb-20 px-6">
    <article class="max-w-[720px] mx-auto">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors mb-8"
      >
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M12 4L4 12M4 4h8M4 4v8"/>
        </svg>
        Back to tryskilly.app
      </a>

      <span class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-amber-500 tracking-[1.5px] uppercase">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-50 mt-3 mb-4">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 mb-10">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 leading-relaxed">
          <strong>Draft.</strong> This is a plain-English draft covering how the Skilly Beta currently works. A final, generator-produced version will replace this before we exit beta.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-gray-300">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">1. Who can use Skilly</h2>
          <p>
            You must be at least 13 years old and able to form a binding contract in your jurisdiction. Skilly is provided to individuals. If you're using it on behalf of an organization, you confirm you have authority to bind that organization to these terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">2. The Skilly Beta program</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            Skilly is currently offered as a time-boxed beta program limited to the first 50 users. Joining the beta gives you:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 marker:text-amber-500">
            <li>Access to the Skilly macOS application</li>
            <li>Three (3) hours of live voice teaching per calendar month</li>
            <li>The "beta for life" price lock described in Section 3</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">3. Pricing, billing, and the beta lock</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            The Skilly Beta is <strong class="text-gray-50">$19 per month</strong>, billed in advance. Billing is handled by our payments processor, Polar (polar.sh). You can cancel at any time from your Skilly account; cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-3">
            When your monthly allowance of three hours is exhausted, Skilly pauses live teaching until your next billing cycle. You are never charged above the subscription price — there are no overage fees.
          </p>
          <p>
            As long as you remain a continuously active subscriber, your beta price ($19/month for 3 hours) is locked for the lifetime of your subscription, even after the beta ends and new pricing tiers are introduced. If you cancel and resubscribe later, the current public pricing applies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">4. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">Please don't use Skilly to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 marker:text-amber-500">
            <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or otherwise extract our prompts, models, or proprietary code</li>
            <li>Abuse, threaten, or harass anyone through the service</li>
            <li>Share a single account across multiple people</li>
            <li>Resell access to Skilly or its underlying APIs</li>
            <li>Attempt to circumvent the usage cap or billing system</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">5. Beta software disclaimer</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            Skilly is beta software. It may have bugs, downtime, and unexpected behavior. We'll try hard to keep it reliable, but we provide it <strong class="text-gray-50">"as is"</strong> and make no warranties about availability, accuracy, or fitness for a particular purpose.
          </p>
          <p>
            Skilly is a teaching assistant, not a replacement for your own judgment. Don't run destructive actions you don't understand just because Skilly suggested them.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">6. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, moelabs.dev (the maker of Skilly) is not liable for indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the service. Our total aggregate liability to you for any claim is limited to the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the event giving rise to the claim.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">7. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            You can cancel your subscription at any time. We can terminate your account if you violate these terms or abuse the service. On termination, your access ends immediately and any remaining time in the current billing period is not refunded (except where required by law).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">8. Changes to these terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms as the product evolves. Material changes will be communicated via email to your account address. Continued use after the effective date of a change constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-50 mb-3">9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hello@tryskilly.app" class="text-amber-500 hover:text-amber-400 underline underline-offset-2">hello@tryskilly.app</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-800">
        See also: <a href="/privacy" class="text-amber-500 hover:text-amber-400 underline underline-offset-2">Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
